-- ==========================================================================
--
--  1. STONE DUALITY AXIOM (tex Axiom AxStoneDuality, line 282)
--
-- ==========================================================================
--
-- The Stone Duality Axiom states that for every countably presented
-- Boolean algebra B : Booleω, the evaluation map
--
--     eval_B : ⟨ B ⟩ → (Sp B → Bool)
--
-- is an equivalence.  Here Sp B is the spectrum of B, i.e., the type
-- of Boolean ring homomorphisms B → 2.
--
-- Re-exported from Part02/Axioms.StoneDuality:
--   StoneDualityAxiom : Type (ℓ-suc ℓ-zero)
--   Sp     : Booleω → Type ℓ-zero          (spectrum functor)
--   Booleω : Type (ℓ-suc ℓ-zero)           (countably presented Boolean algebras)
--   SpEmbedding : StoneDualityAxiom → isEmbedding Sp
--
-- Postulated axiom:
--   sd-axiom : StoneDualityAxiom            (Part02, line 835)

-- ==========================================================================
--
--  2. SURJECTIONS ARE FORMAL SURJECTIONS (tex Axiom SurjectionsAreFormalSurjections, line 294)
--
-- ==========================================================================
--
-- For all morphisms g : B → C in Booleω:
--   g is injective  ⟺  Sp(g) is surjective.
--
-- This axiom connects algebraic injectivity to topological surjectivity,
-- and is essential for the LLPO proof.
--
-- Re-exported from Part02:
--   SurjectionsAreFormalSurjectionsAxiom : Type (ℓ-suc ℓ-zero)
--   surj-formal-axiom : SurjectionsAreFormalSurjectionsAxiom
--   isInjectiveBoolHom  : (B C : Booleω) → BoolHom (fst B) (fst C) → Type ℓ-zero
--   isSurjectiveSpHom   : (B C : Booleω) → BoolHom (fst B) (fst C) → Type ℓ-zero
--   Sp-hom              : (B C : Booleω) → BoolHom (fst B) (fst C) → Sp C → Sp B
--   injective→Sp-surjective : ...  (forward direction)
--   Sp-surjective→injective : ...  (backward direction)

-- ==========================================================================
--
--  3. LOCAL CHOICE (tex Axiom AxLocalChoice, line 348)
--
-- ==========================================================================
--
-- For all B : Booleω and type family P over Sp(B), if
--   (s : Sp B) → ∥ P s ∥₁
-- then there merely exists C : Booleω, a surjection q : Sp C → Sp B,
-- and untruncated witnesses (t : Sp C) → P (q t).
--
-- This axiom allows "pulling back along a surjection" to eliminate
-- propositional truncation.
--
-- Re-exported from Part02:
--   LocalChoiceAxiom  : Type (ℓ-suc ℓ-zero)
--   localChoice-axiom : LocalChoiceAxiom
--   SpTypeFamily      : Booleω → Type (ℓ-suc ℓ-zero)
--   isSurjectiveSpMap : {B C : Booleω} → (Sp C → Sp B) → Type ℓ-zero

