--
-- ==========================================================================
--
-- For all types (Eₙ)_{n:ℕ} with surjections E_{n+1} ↠ Eₙ,
-- the projection from lim_k Eₖ to E₀ is surjective.
--
-- Re-exported from Part02:
--   DependentChoiceAxiom  : Type (ℓ-suc ℓ-zero)
--   dependentChoice-axiom : DependentChoiceAxiom
--   SeqLimit   : (E : ℕ → Type ℓ-zero) → ((n : ℕ) → E (suc n) → E n) → Type ℓ-zero
--   seqLim-proj₀ : ...
--
-- Derived:
--   CountableChoiceAxiom : Type (ℓ-suc ℓ-zero)
--   countableChoice      : CountableChoiceAxiom
--                          (derived from DependentChoice, Part02 line 946)

-- ==========================================================================
--
--  5. CONSEQUENCE: MARKOV'S PRINCIPLE (tex Theorem MPfromSD, line 459)
--
-- ==========================================================================
--
-- For all α : 2^ℕ:
--   ¬(∀ n, α n = false) → Σ[ n ∈ ℕ ] α n = true
--
-- Proof sketch (from tex, lines 459-468):
--   1. ¬(∀n. αn = false) means Sp(2/α) is empty (MarkovLib.emptySp).
--   2. Stone Duality (Sp is an embedding) gives 2/α = trivial ring.
--   3. Hence 0 = 1 in 2/α, so true ∈ ideal generated by α.
--   4. By MarkovLib.extract', this yields Σn. αn = true.
--
-- Re-exported from Part02:
--   MarkovPrinciple : Type₀                  (Part01, line 347)
--   mp              : MarkovPrinciple         (Part02, line 985)
--   mp-from-SD      : StoneDualityAxiom → MarkovPrinciple
--
-- Infrastructure used in the proof:
--   SpectrumEmptyImpliesTrivial : module      (Part02, line 58)
--   quotient-Booleω : binarySequence → Booleω (Part02, line 830)

-- ==========================================================================
--
--  6. CONSEQUENCE: LLPO (tex Theorem LLPO, lines 541-595)
--
-- ==========================================================================
--
-- For all α : ℕ∞ (sequences hitting true at most once):
--   (∀ k, α_{2k} = false) ⊎ (∀ k, α_{2k+1} = false)
--
-- The proof constructs f : B∞ → B∞ × B∞, shows it is injective
-- (via normal forms), then uses SurjectionsAreFormalSurjections to get
-- that Sp(f) is surjective.  Case-splitting on the preimage yields LLPO.
--
-- The full proof with documentation is in work/LLPOWork.agda.
--
-- Re-exported from Part02:
--   LLPO            : Type₀                   (Part01, line 399)
--   llpo            : LLPO                    (Part02, postulate, line 1220)
--   hitsAtMostOnce  : binarySequence → Type₀  (Part01, line 388)
--   ℕ∞              : Type₀                   (Part01, line 396)

-- ==========================================================================
--
--  7. CONSEQUENCE: ¬WLPO (tex Theorem NotWLPO, line 475)
--
-- ==========================================================================
--
-- ¬ ∀ α : 2^ℕ, ((∀ n, α n = false) ∨ ¬(∀ n, α n = false))
--
-- Proof sketch (from tex, lines 475-497):
--   1. Assume f : 2^ℕ → Bool decides "all zeros":
--        f(α) = false ↔ ∀n. αn = false
--   2. By Stone Duality, f is determined by a Boolean term c
--      using only finitely many generators g₀, ..., gₖ.
--   3. Consider β = 0^ω (all zeros) and γ = 0^k 1 0^ω.
--   4. β and γ agree on g₀, ..., gₖ, so f(β) = f(γ).
--   5. But f(β) should be false and f(γ) should be true.
--   6. Contradiction.
--
-- Re-exported from Part01:
--   WLPO : Type₀                             (Part01, line 359)

